  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: 2021.07.5-alpha\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Debian GNU/Linux 10 (buster)\r\n\r\nCommit hash: 63a6c45ef1f998f8c74d38d19b6c57835ebdf977\r\n\r\nI start the daemon like this:\r\n```bash\r\n$ build/bin/erigon --private.api.addr=127.0.0.1:9090 --verbosity=5 --chain=dev --miner.etherbase=00a329c0648769a73afac7f9381e08fb43dbea72\r\n```\r\nAnd the RPC daemon like this:\r\n```bash\r\n$ build/bin/rpcdaemon --private.api.addr=127.0.0.1:9090 --verbosity=5 --http.api=eth,web3,txpool\r\n```\r\nFunds are showing up OK in the dev address:\r\n```bash\r\n$ curl -s -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\r\n\t--data '{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"eth_getBalance\", \"params\": [\"0x00a329c0648769a73afac7f9381e08fb43dbea72\",\"latest\"], \"id\":1}' \\\r\n\tlocalhost:8545 | jq -M '.'\r\n```\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n\t\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n\t\"id\": 1,\r\n\t\"result\": \"0xfffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffff7\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\nBut when I try to send a transaction, the call hangs:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n$ curl -s -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\r\n\t--data '{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"eth_sendRawTransaction\", \"params\": [\"0xf86f80850ba43b7400825208941f2f0641c80c1f6a13edf22e184292584ddcc9d98906b14bd1e6eea0000080820a96a09d16d88269ca9ccd2bfd7ec90c63424f4107c10b183d00f7335b85619f019751a05b71382c8d025526f11c87fb5de0a148f727ec0c3d9e6a604b59c83307ae58e4\"], \"id\":1}' \\\r\n\tlocalhost:8545\r\n```\r\n(Ctrl-C)\r\n\r\nChecking the txpool, I see that the transaction is queued rather than pending, which shouldn’t be happening, since the nonce is zero:\r\n```bash\r\n$ curl -s -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\r\n\t--data '{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"txpool_content\", \"params\": [], \"id\":1}' \\\r\n\tlocalhost:8545 | jq -M '.'\r\n```\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n\t\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n\t\"id\": 1,\r\n\t\"result\": {\r\n\t\t\"pending\": {},\r\n\t\t\"queued\": {\r\n\t\t\t\"0x00a329c0648769A73afAc7F9381E08FB43dBEA72\": {\r\n\t\t\t\t\"0\": {\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"blockHash\": null,\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"blockNumber\": null,\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"from\": \"0x00a329c0648769a73afac7f9381e08fb43dbea72\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"gas\": \"0x5208\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"gasPrice\": \"0xba43b7400\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"hash\": \"0x797cd07b29aef1049236dc853875a0e7f586da19528450aed9601712f5c7b4f6\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"input\": \"0x\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"nonce\": \"0x0\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"to\": \"0x1f2f0641c80c1f6a13edf22e184292584ddcc9d9\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"transactionIndex\": null,\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"value\": \"0x6b14bd1e6eea00000\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"type\": \"0x0\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"v\": \"0xa96\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"r\": \"0x9d16d88269ca9ccd2bfd7ec90c63424f4107c10b183d00f7335b85619f019751\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"s\": \"0x5b71382c8d025526f11c87fb5de0a148f727ec0c3d9e6a604b59c83307ae58e4\"\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n```\r\nNot surprisingly, the blockchain never advances, as the daemon output shows:\r\n```log\r\nINFO [07-30|19:37:04.794] Build info                               git_branch=devel git_tag=v2021.07.04-25-g63a6c45ef git_commit=63a6c45ef1f998f8c74d38d19b6c57835ebdf977\r\nINFO [07-30|19:37:04.794] Starting Erigon in ephemeral dev mode...\r\nINFO [07-30|19:37:04.795] Maximum peer count                       ETH=100 total=100\r\nINFO [07-30|19:37:04.795] Set global gas cap                       cap=50000000\r\nINFO [07-30|19:37:04.795] Using developer account                  address=0x00a329c0648769A73afAc7F9381E08FB43dBEA72\r\nINFO [07-30|19:37:04.815] Writing custom genesis block             hash=0x8064b3b7fa03f3a660d6b72229483faa73e89bd222f50c9077c1c847a91831e8\r\nINFO [07-30|19:37:04.819] Initialised chain configuration          config=\"{ChainID: 1337 Homestead: 0 DAO: <nil> DAOSupport: false EIP150: 0 EIP155: 0 EIP158: 0 Byzantium: 0 Constantinople: 0 Petersburg: 0 Istanbul: 0, Muir Glacier: 0, Berlin: 0, London: <nil>, Engine: clique}\"\r\nINFO [07-30|19:37:04.823] Initialising Ethereum protocol           network=1337\r\nINFO [07-30|19:37:04.823] Effective                                prune=\"history=no,receipt=no,txindex=no,calltrace=no,experiments.tevm=disabled\"\r\nINFO [07-30|19:37:04.827] Starting private RPC server              on=127.0.0.1:9090\r\n...\r\nINFO [07-30|19:37:04.860] Started P2P networking                   version=65 self=\"enode://d804a426f2ffcac6fa817b0c044243e085d4bfaaecd723b3e53413eef013f242973aa68bf36ab9912b5e32d75213a86a66ea3671ab28f7b9f8e381cc5209f3e2@127.0.0.1:30304?discport=0\" name=erigon/v2021.07.5-alpha-63a6c45e/linux-amd64/go1.16.6\r\n...\r\nINFO [07-30|19:37:20.050] Setting new local account                address=0x00a329c0648769A73afAc7F9381E08FB43dBEA72\r\nTRACE[07-30|19:37:20.051] Pooled new future transaction            hash=\"797cd0…c7b4f6\" from=0x00a329c0648769A73afAc7F9381E08FB43dBEA72 to=0x1f2F0641c80c1f6A13Edf22E184292584Ddcc9D9\r\n...\r\nDEBUG[07-30|19:37:20.853] Request skeleton                         anchors=0 top seen height=0 highestInDb=0\r\n...\r\nDEBUG[07-30|19:37:21.854] Request skeleton                         anchors=0 top seen height=0 highestInDb=0\r\n...\r\nDEBUG[07-30|19:37:22.855] Request skeleton                         anchors=0 top seen height=0 highestInDb=0\r\n...\r\nDEBUG[07-30|19:37:23.857] Request skeleton                         anchors=0 top seen height=0 highestInDb=0\r\n...\r\nDEBUG[07-30|19:37:24.858] Request skeleton                         anchors=0 top seen height=0 highestInDb=0\r\n...\r\nDEBUG[07-30|19:37:25.859] Request skeleton                         anchors=0 top seen height=0 highestInDb=0\r\n...\r\nDEBUG[07-30|19:37:26.860] Request skeleton                         anchors=0 top seen height=0 highestInDb=0\r\n...\r\nDEBUG[07-30|19:37:27.860] Request skeleton                         anchors=0 top seen height=0 highestInDb=0\r\n```\r\nBy applying the following patch, I see that clique.period == 0, as it should be, so that’s not the problem:\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/core/genesis.go b/core/genesis.go\r\nindex c30f1d39c..aef0f8e3c 100644\r\n--- a/core/genesis.go\r\n+++ b/core/genesis.go\r\n@@ -621,6 +621,7 @@ func DeveloperGenesisBlock(period uint64, faucet common.Address) *Genesis {\r\n\t// Override the default period to the user requested one\r\n\tconfig := *params.AllCliqueProtocolChanges\r\n\tconfig.Clique.Period = period\r\n+\tlog.Info(\"User debug\",\"config.Clique.Period\", config.Clique.Period)\r\n\r\n\t// Assemble and return the genesis with the precompiles and faucet pre-funded\r\n\treturn &Genesis{\r\n```\r\nIn developer mode blocks should be mined automatically with each new pending transaction if the period is set to 0. However, the transaction is never mined as it remains stuck in the queue. What am I missing here?\r\n",
